Dear Steven,

1. is p1 / p4
2. is p2 / p4
3. is p3 / p4

So, p4 / p1 is just the reciprocal of 1. (i.e. 1/.81).

The rest is just some simple algebra:

(p2/p4) / (p1/p4) = p2 / p1
(p3/p4) / (p1/p4) = p3 / p1

Best,
Wolfgang

